# Keeps the Docker build context small for tools/trustsc-medui-studio/Dockerfile, which builds
# from the repo root (the crate is a workspace member, so the whole workspace is the build
# context). None of this is needed inside the image: build output, VCS metadata, and the
# frontend's own node_modules (frontend/dist/ — the actual build output the server embeds — is
# committed and copied normally). generated/fonts, generated/images, and generated/models are
# NOT excluded here: they're real build.rs inputs the release binary is baked from.
/target
.git
**/node_modules

# ADR-016 --verify-ui evidence (gitignored, regenerated fresh every run) and the wave S7
# self-test's preview PNG (also gitignored, written to whatever directory it's run from) — never
# build inputs, and can be large/plentiful if this checkout has been used to run either locally.
# Scoped to these known-generated paths rather than a blanket **/*.png: a future baked image
# fixture could legitimately need to be a real build input in the Docker context.
/generated/verification/
/self-test-preview.png
